The paper discusses compressed full-text self-indexes, which are a type of data structure used for efficient text indexing and retrieval. This topic falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also mentions the need for programming skills and algorithmic background, which suggests a focus on computer science theory (cs.CC) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation and deployment of compressed indexes, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
